"tlg0007_tlg112.T141553" [label=<<b>THESIS</b><br/>          Plutarchus          <br/>691b<br/><i>When rubbed with vinegar, lead sends forth the<br/>most cooling of deadly drugs, i.e., lead white<br/></i><font point-size="12">"ὅ τε μόλιβδος ... ἐξανίησι ψιμύθιον"</font>>, gephi_label="THES", locus="691b", speaker="Plutarchus", text="ὅ τε μόλιβδος ... ὅς γε τριβόμενος ὄξει τὸ ψυκτικώτατον τῶν θανασίμων φαρμάκων ἐξανίησι ψιμύθιον", paraphrasis="When rubbed with vinegar, lead sends forth the most cooling of deadly drugs, i.e., lead white ", manifestation="explicit", source="tlg0007_tlg112", fillcolor="#f0faf0", color="#82b366", style="rounded,filled", shape="box", margin="0.30,0.1"];

